      <p class="text-xl text-gray-500">In a mist-soaked realm where limestone pinnacles pierce clouds at 1,800 meters and tea trees older than empires twist through primordial forest, the H'Mông and Dao guardians harvest leaves of impossible complexity — <em>Shan Tuyet</em>, the snow-covered mountain tea.</p>
